# AgentMesh Full-Stack Example — Environment Variables

# Optional: set to enable LLM-powered policy extraction (Layer 2).
# When set, the coordinator uses Claude (claude-haiku-4-5-20251001) to parse
# the task description into structured capabilities and constraints.
# Without this, rule-based keyword extraction is used (works fine for demos).
# Requires: pip install anthropic
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# Task description for the coordinator (used by demo.py)
TASK="Validate, analyze, and report on a dataset"

# Maximum budget for task execution (USD)
BUDGET=0.10

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Authentication (recommended for production)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Symmetric secret used for HMAC-SHA256 session token generation.
# Workers use this to verify that ExecuteStep requests came from a coordinator
# that completed a legitimate negotiation exchange.
# Generate a secure value:
#   python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"
# AGENTMESH_TOKEN_SECRET=your-long-random-hex-value-here

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Layer 6 — Attestation Backend (optional)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# By default, execution-step integrity proofs are stored in-memory
# (LocalHashBackend).  Set the variables below to enable on-chain or
# JSON-RPC attestation.

# --- Option A: JSON-RPC attestation (any compatible HTTP endpoint) --------
# Sends a JSON-RPC "attest" call after every step; falls back to local on error.
# ATTESTATION_RPC_URL=http://my-attestation-server:8080/attest

# --- Option B: Filecoin/FEVM on-chain attestation -------------------------
# Submits a transaction to a deployed FVM actor for cryptographic audit trail.
# Requires: pip install web3  (and activate the web3 block in attestation.py)
# FEVM_RPC_URL=https://api.calibration.node.glif.io/rpc/v1
# FEVM_CONTRACT=0xYourContractAddress
# FEVM_PRIVATE_KEY=0xYourHexPrivateKey
